title: YirumaVEVO
desc:
Yiruma was born on Feb 15, 1978 and started to learn
 the piano at
 home at the age of 5. In 1988 at the age of 11 he
 moved to England
 to study at the Purcell School of Music. In December
 1996 he
 participated in the album The Musicians of Purcell
 and graduated
 in 1997. Yiruma then completed a Composition major
 from the
 prestigious King's College London in 2000. While
 studying at Kings
 College, Yiruma released his first album Love Scene
 and toured
 Europe. He was the first Korean artist to be
 honoured with an
 invitation to perform at the 2002 MIDEM in Cannes,
 France. Yiruma
 has gone on to release 7 studio albums and compose
 soundtracks for
 musicals, films and theatre. His YouTube channel has
 had over 124
 million hits and he has also found success as a
 radio DJ. Yiruma
 continues to tour and record through Europe and Asia
 where he is
 enjoying superstar status.

desc:
Hi, my name is Steve, and welcome to my channel. I
 create Math
 Rock based guitar lessons, gear reviews, and general
 guitar
 videos. While I'm no connoisseur of Math Rock, I am
 a huge fan of
 the style, and a lot of my guitar playing is
 inspired by it. I'd
 say my wheelhouse is the blending between Math Rock
 and emo
 styles. This is what often interests me the most.
 Outside of this,
 I am interested in telecasters, guitars in general,
 and effect
 pedals! So you'll see video about the popping up
 from time to
 time. Overall, my aims with this channel are to get
 you thinking
 about methods and techniques for improving your song
 writing
 skills, theory knowledge and your technique. Thank
 you for taking
 the time to check out my channel.
